"title": "8356: unselfishness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8356",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Putting the concerns and interests of others before one's own. Jesus Christ was the supreme example of this and believers should follow his example, denying themselves in order to serve others.</p>\n<h2>The supreme example of selflessness is that of Jesus Christ himself</h2>\n<h3>In his life and work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:30\">JHN 5:30</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:3\">ROM 15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:32\">MAT 15:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:3-John13:5\">JHN 13:3–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a></p>\n<h3>In his dying for others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:26-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:26–20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:43-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:43–10:45</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:5–2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:3-Isa53:12\">ISA 53:3–53:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:17-John10:18\">JHN 10:17–10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6-Rom5:8\">ROM 5:6–5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3\">1CO 15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:14\">2CO 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:10\">1TH 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22-1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:22–2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:6\">1TI 2:6</a></p>\n<h2>Unselfishness is a result of a relationship with Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Christian discipleship begins with a denial of self-interest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:6\">ROM 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22\">EPH 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:9\">COL 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>It springs from an experience of life with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:21-Phil1:24\">PHP 1:21–1:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:7-Phil3:11\">PHP 3:7–3:11</a></p>\n<h3>It is inspired by the example of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:4-Phil2:5\">PHP 2:4–2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:14-John13:15\">JHN 13:14–13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:16\">1JN 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:19-1John4:21\">1JN 4:19–4:21</a></p>\n<h3>It is the result of the Spirit's work in the believer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:26\">GAL 5:22–5:26</a></p>\n<h2>Putting others first is fundamental in Christian behaviour</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:10\">ROM 12:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:23-1Cor10:24\">1CO 10:23–10:24</a></strong> <em>This was particularly so when it came to the exercise of personal scruples.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:7\">ROM 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:1-Rom15:2\">ROM 15:1–15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:9\">1CO 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32-Eph5:2\">EPH 4:32–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13\">COL 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:18\">1TI 6:18</a></p>\n<h2>Unselfishness involves a proper attitude to one's own self-importance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:3\">PHP 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:16\">ROM 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:2-Gal6:3\">GAL 6:2–6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:2\">EPH 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:21\">EPH 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:8\">1PE 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Unselfishness is expressed in Christian service</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:26\">LUK 22:26</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:13\">GAL 5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10\">1PE 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of unselfish behaviour</h2>\n<h3>Those who put others first</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:8-Gen13:9\">GEN 13:8–13:9</a> <em>Abraham</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:31-Exod32:32\">EXO 32:31–32:32</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:16-Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:16–1:17</a> <em>Ruth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:3-1Sam12:5\">1SA 12:3–12:5</a> <em>Samuel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:14-Neh5:18\">NEH 5:14–5:18</a> <em>Nehemiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:41-Mark12:44\">MRK 12:41–12:44</a> <em>a poor widow</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a> <em>a mother</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:6-Matt26:13\">MAT 26:6–26:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3-Mark14:9\">MRK 14:3–14:9</a> <em>a woman with a jar of perfume</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:27-John3:30\">JHN 3:27–3:30</a> <em>John the Baptist</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:32-Acts4:37\">ACT 4:32–4:37</a> <em>the first Christians</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:3-Rom16:4\">ROM 16:3–16:4</a> <em>Priscilla and Aquila</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:15\">1CO 16:15</a> <em>the household of Stephanas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:20-Phil2:21\">PHP 2:20–2:21</a> <em>Timothy</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:29-Phil2:30\">PHP 2:29–2:30</a> <em>Epaphroditus</em></p>\n<h3>Paul's ministry was motivated by the interests of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:32-1Cor10:33\">1CO 10:32–10:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:1\">1CO 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:33-Acts20:35\">ACT 20:33–20:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:3-1Cor9:15\">1CO 9:3–9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:19-1Cor9:23\">1CO 9:19–9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:23-2Cor11:29\">2CO 11:23–11:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:4\">2CO 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:17\">PHP 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:8-1Thess2:9\">1TH 2:8–2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:19-1Thess2:20\">1TH 2:19–2:20</a></p>",
